    "content": "NATIVE_GAUNTLET MEDIUM T6_NATIVE_MEDIUM_20260523\n\nMaya, this is a native repo task for /Users/gaganarora/Desktop/my projects/active_graph/activegraph.\n\n1. cd into activegraph/. Confirm pwd and `git rev-parse --short HEAD`.\n2. Capture baseline pytest collected-test count:\n     uv run pytest --collect-only -q 2>&1 | tail -3\n   Record the integer count as `pytest_collect_before`.\n3. Pick ONE public API surface in activegraph/activegraph/ that is currently\n   NOT covered by any file in activegraph/tests/. Prove the gap by running:\n     uv run pytest --collect-only -q -k <symbol> 2>&1\n   It must show 0 collected tests for that symbol. Record the chosen symbol\n   as `uncovered_symbol` (use the fully qualified name, e.g.\n   activegraph.module.Class.method).\n4. Write activegraph/tests/test_<feature>_coverage.py with AT LEAST 2 test\n   functions exercising distinct configurations of the API (e.g. happy path\n   plus one boundary or error condition). Use real fixtures, not mocks of\n   the API under test. Each test function name should include enough of\n   <uncovered_symbol> that `pytest --collect-only -k <uncovered_symbol>`\n   matches it.\n5. Run the new test file alone:\n     uv run pytest activegraph/tests/test_<feature>_coverage.py -v\n   All tests must pass.\n6. Run the full pytest suite:\n     uv run pytest -q --tb=no 2>&1 | tail -3\n   - `pytest_after` (passing count) MUST be greater than or equal to\n     `pytest_before` (use 696 from the existing baseline at\n     frames/t6-pytest-baseline-20260523.txt).\n   - `pytest_collect_after - pytest_collect_before` MUST EQUAL the number\n     of new test functions you added in step 4 (catches accidentally\n     hidden tests).\n7. Confirm `pytest --collect-only -k <uncovered_symbol>` now returns AT\n   LEAST 2 collected tests at HEAD.\n8. Commit the new test file in the activegraph/ inner repo with message:\n     T6 medium: cover <uncovered_symbol>\n   Record the resulting commit SHA as `agent_commit_sha`.\n9. Run `uv run ruff check activegraph/tests/test_<feature>_coverage.py` --\n   must exit 0. Record as `ruff_target_exit`.\n10. Create frames/t6-native-gauntlet-medium-20260523.proof (relative path\n    may live at frames/ or activegraph/frames/; either is accepted by the\n    verifier) with EXACTLY these keys, in this order:\n      hash=T6_NATIVE_MEDIUM_20260523\n      pwd=<pwd output>\n      head=<git short head>\n      uncovered_symbol=<fully.qualified.name>\n      test_file=activegraph/tests/test_<feature>_coverage.py\n      new_test_count=<int>\n      pytest_collect_before=<int>\n      pytest_collect_after=<int>\n      pytest_before=<int>\n      pytest_after=<int>\n      agent_commit_sha=<full sha that committed test_file>\n      ruff_target_exit=0\n      verdict=native_medium_done\n11. Reply exactly:\n    MAYA_NATIVE_GAUNTLET_ACK T6_NATIVE_MEDIUM_20260523 MEDIUM frames/t6-native-gauntlet-medium-20260523.proof\n",
